import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.title("What is the correlation between 'u' and 'v'?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['u'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label="u distribution")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel("u")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'u'?")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['v'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label="Frequency")
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel("v")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'v'?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['u'])
    mean_u = data['u'].mean()
    std_u = data['u'].std()
    ax.axhline(mean_u, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {mean_u:.2f}")
    ax.axhline(mean_u + std_u, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean + 1 Std: {mean_u + std_u:.2f}")
    ax.axhline(mean_u - std_u, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean - 1 Std: {mean_u - std_u:.2f}")
    ax.set_title("What is the mean and standard deviation of 'u'?")
    ax.set_ylabel("Values of 'u'")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
